But to confirm this certain Truth from a more substantial Authority than my own. 'Tis the very Opinion of the Reverend Dr. Burnet himfelf,
                a person, let me tell you, under no small Pains-taking for the protestant Religion, and as a Churchman, under no common Consternation from popish Dangers,
                and therefore not at all likely to lull us into a false Security of our Religion. The Instance of which Opinion I find in the 9th. page of his Preface to the Rights of Princes, as follows;
